  "prompt": "I've only heard one song by Jackson Browne which I totally loved! 'Late for the sky'! Can anyone recommend me more Jackson Browne songs? Even albums?",
  "response": "Absolutely! Jackson Browne is a fantastic artist, and *\"Late for the Sky\"* is a masterpiece. Here are some more songs and albums you might enjoy based on your love for that track:\n\n### **Songs You\u2019ll Likely Enjoy:**\n1. **\"These Days\"** \u2013 A somber, reflective ballad that\u2019s both poetic and haunting.  \n2. **\"Fountain of Sorrow\"** \u2013 A deeply introspective song with beautiful storytelling.  \n3. **\"The Pretender\"** \u2013 A powerful track that blends contemplation with a driving rhythm.  \n4. **\"Running on Empty\"** \u2013 A more upbeat but still poignant anthem about life on the road.  \n5. **\"For a Dancer\"** \u2013 A moving tribute to life, loss, and resilience.  \n6. **\"Before the Deluge\"** \u2013 A spiritual and philosophical song with lush melodies.  \n7. **\"Doctor My Eyes\"** \u2013 One of his early hits, blending folk-rock with introspective lyrics.  \n\n### **Albums to Explore:**\n1. **\"Late for the Sky\" (1974)** \u2013 The album with your favorite song! It\u2019s a cohesive masterpiece of introspection and beauty.  \n2. **\"The Pretender\" (1976)** \u2013 A mix of melancholy and resilience, exploring themes of love, loss, and hope.  \n3. **\"Running on Empty\" (1977)** \u2013 A live/studio hybrid album capturing life on the road, with raw energy and emotional depth.  \n4. **\"For Everyman\" (1973)** \u2013 His second album, filled with poetic lyrics and folk-rock vibes.  \n5. **\"Jackson Browne (Saturate Before Using)\" (1972)** \u2013 His debut album, featuring classics like **\"Doctor My Eyes\"** and **\"Rock Me on the Water.\"**  \n6. **\"Hold Out\" (1980)** \u2013 A more rock-oriented album with tracks like **\"Boulevard\"** and **\"Call It a Loan.\"**  \n\n### **Bonus:**  \nIf you love the introspective and poetic side of *\"Late for the Sky,\"* you might also enjoy his collaborations with other artists, like his work with **The Eagles** (he co-wrote their hit **\"Take It Easy\"**) or his duets with **Bonnie Raitt**.\n\nHappy listening! Jackson Browne\u2019s music is a treasure trove of emotional and lyrical depth. \ud83c\udf1f",
